    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="75"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d75">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Lauchlin Currie</persName> to
                        President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="24" type="source" xml:id="d75fn24">Photostatic copy obtained from the
                        Franklin D. Roosevelt Library, Hyde Park, N. Y.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-01">June 1,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">Re: Attached cable from Madame Chiang Kai-shek.<note n="25"
                        xml:id="d75fn25">Dated May 31, <ref target="#pg_60">p. 60</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I think the reason behind this request is not so much for consultation as for
                    morale boosting, and as such would be very desirable.</p>
                <p>If Mr. Hopkins goes I do not think my presence would add a lot. On the other
                    hand, if Mr. Hopkins is unable to go I believe I still have a lot of prestige in
                    China as your representative.</p>
                <p>You will note that an immediate reply is requested.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Laugh Currie</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
